Kent Walker, Google\'s senior vice-president of global affairs, said the company had \xe2\x80\x9calready made a wide range of changes to our products to address the Commission\xe2\x80\x99s concerns,\xe2\x80\x9d and that "we\'ll be making further updates to give more visibility to rivals in Europe."\n       <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-300">\n        <a href="#cite_note-300">\n         [299]\n        </a>\n       </sup>\n      </p>\n      <p>\n       On July 25, 2019, presidential hopeful\n       <a href="/wiki/Tulsi_Gabbard" title="Tulsi Gabbard">\n        Tulsi Gabbard\n       </a>\n       sued Google for blocking her ads after the presidential debate when she became one of the most searched items on the search engine.\n       <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-301">\n        <a href="#cite_note-301">\n         [300]\n        </a>\n       </sup>\n      </p>\n      <h3>\n       <span class="mw-headline" id="DeGoogle_movement">\n        DeGoogle movement\n       </span>\n      </h3>\n      <div class="hatnote navigation-not-searchable" role="note">\n       Main article:\n       <a href="/wiki/DeGoogle" title="DeGoogle">\n        DeGoogle\n       </a>\n      </div>\n      <p>\n       The term "\n       <a href="/wiki/DeGoogle" title="DeGoogle">\n        DeGoogle\n       </a>\n       " has grown in use as\n       <a href="/wiki/Privacy" title="Privacy">\n        privacy\n       </a>\n       activists urge users to stop using Google products entirely due to\n       <a href="/wiki/Privacy_concerns_regarding_Google" title="Privacy concerns regarding Google">\n        growing privacy concerns\n       </a>\n       .\n       <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-302">\n        <a href="#cite_note-302">\n         [301]\n        </a>\n       </sup>\n       <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-303">\n        <a href="#cite_note-303">\n         [302]\n        </a>\n       </sup>\n       The term refers to the act of removing Google from your life.\n      </p>\n      <h2>\n       <span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">\n        See also\n       </span>\n      </h2>\n      <ul>\n       <li>\n        <a href="/wiki/Outline_of_Google" title="Outline of <a href="/wiki/Portal:Internet" title="Portal:Internet">\n           Internet portal\n          </a>\n         </span>\n        </li>\n        <li style="display:inline">\n         <span      <li style="display:inline">\n         <span style="display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap">\n          <span style="margin:0 0.5em">\n           <a class="image" //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/SF_From_Marin_Highlands3.jpg/48px-SF_From_Marin_Highlands3.jpg 2x" width="24"/>\n           </a>\n          </span>\n          <a href="/wiki/Portal:San_Francisco_Bay_Area" title="Portal:San Francisco Bay Area">\n           San Francisco Bay Area portal\n          </a>\n         </span>\n        </li>\n        <li style="display:inline">\n         <span style="display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap">\n          <span style="margin:0 0.5em">\n           <a class="image" href="/wiki/File:Telecom-icon.svg">\n            <img alt="Telecom-icon.svg" data-file-height="500" data-file-width="500" decoding="async" height="21" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Telecom-icon.svg/21px-Telecom-icon.svg.png" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Telecom-icon.svg/32px-Telecom-icon.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4e/Telecom-icon.svg/42px-Telecom-icon.svg.png 2x" width="21"/>\n           </a>\n          </span>\n          <a href="/wiki/Portal:Technology" title="Portal:Technology">\n           Technology portal\n          </a>\n         </span>\n        </li>\n        <li style="display:inline">\n         <span style="display:inline-block;white-space:nowrap">\n          <span style="margin:0 0.5em">\n           <a class="image" href="/wiki/File:Octicons-terminal.svg">\n            <img  <h2>\n       <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">\n        Notes\n       </span>\n      </h2>\n      <div class="reflist" style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">\n       <div class="mw-references-wrap">\n        <ol class="references">\n         <li id="cite_note-5">\n          <span class="mw-cite-backlink">\n           <b>\n            <a href="#cite_ref-5">\n             ^\n            </a>\n           </b>\n          </span>\n          <span class="reference-text">\n           Google was originally incorporated on September 4, 1998, however, since 2002, the company has celebrated its anniversaries on various days in September, most frequently on September 27.\n           <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-1">\n            <a href="#cite_note-1">\n             [1]\n            </a>\n           </sup>\n           <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-2">\n            <a href="#cite_note-2">\n             [2]\n            </a>\n           </sup>\n           <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-3">\n            <a href="#cite_note-3">\n             [3]\n            </a>\n           </sup>\n           The shift in dates reportedly happened to celebrate index-size milestones in tandem with the birthday.\n           <sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-4">\n            <a href="#cite_note-4">\n             [4]\n            </a>\n           </sup>\n          </span>\n         </li>\n        </ol>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n      <h2>\n       <span class="mw-headline" id="References">\n        References\n       </span>\n      </h2>\n      <div our applications comes from fashioning a reliable computing infrastructure from clusters of unreliable commodity PCs.\n            </q>\n           </cite>\n           <span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=IEEE+Micro&amp;rft.atitle=Web+search+for+a+planet%3A+the+google+cluster+architecture&amp;rft.volume=23&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=22-28&amp;rft.date=2003-04-29&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1109%2Fmm.2003.1196112&amp;rft.issn=0272-1732&amp;rft.aulast=Barroso&amp;rft.aufirst=L.A.&amp;rft.au=Dean%2C+J.&amp;rft.au=Holzle%2C+U.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fsemanticscholar.org%2Fpaper%2F8db8e53c92af2f97974707119525aa089f6ed53a&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AGoogle">\n   <span class="mw-cite-backlink">\n           ^\n           <a href="#cite_ref-CNET2009_245-0">\n            <sup>\n             <i>\n              <b>\n               a\n              </b>\n             </i>\n            </sup>\n           </a>\n           <a href="#cite_ref-CNET2009_245-1">\n            <sup>\n             <i>\n              <b>\n               b\n              </b>\n             </i>\n            </sup>\n           </a>\n          </span>\n          <span class="reference-text">\n           <cite class="citation news">\n            <a class="external text" Retrieved\n             <span class="nowrap">\n              May 26,\n             </span>\n             2018\n            </span>\n            .\n            <q>\n             Mainstream servers with x86 processors were the only option, he added. "Ten years ago...it was clear the only way to make (search) work as free product was to run on relatively cheap hardware. You can\'t run it on a\n             <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Mainframe_server" title="Mainframe server">\n              mainframe\n             </a>\n             .
